<div>Now is a good time to address one of&nbsp;the few&nbsp;tactics the natural runner knows.</div><div>You run right behind any runner to avoid energy output spent on air resistance.</div><div>It is called drafting, and it is real.</div><div>They say it saves you 7% on energy output.</div><div>Since going a little faster takes a lot of energy,&nbsp;it saves you about 1% on your time (which is significant.)</div>